===Etymology===
Possibly from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*s-ram-s||otter}} ({{zh-ref|Matisoff, 2010}}). If so, cognate with {{cog|bo|སྲམ}}, {{cog|my|ဖျံ}} ({{zh-ref|Hill, 2019}}). See {{zh-ref|Matisoff (2010)}} for a possible explanation for the apparent discrepancy in the coda (Chinese ''-t'' vs. Tibeto-Burman ''-m'').

{{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart (2014)}} posit an optional animal prefix {{m|und|*m-}} as a way to account for the alternation between ''th-'' and ''trh-'' in {{cog|ltc|-}}, citing {{cog|hmn-pro|*ntshju̯aᴬ}}, which shows prenasalization.

{{rfe|zh|related to 猵?}}

